WEBVTT

1
00:00:13.347 --> 00:00:15.598
Oh. my coach just emailed me.

2
00:00:15.599 --> 00:00:17.391
They're redoing the gym at Wesleyan.

3
00:00:17.392 --> 00:00:20.478
so I have to show up for preseason
training. like. right after graduation.

4
00:00:20.479 --> 00:00:21.605
That early?

5
00:00:22.147 --> 00:00:24.649
I knew that fucking coach had it
out for me.

6
00:00:24.650 --> 00:00:26.400
Yeah. she definitely built
the schedule based

7
00:00:26.401 --> 00:00:27.777
on how much it would hurt you.

8
00:00:27.778 --> 00:00:30.112
No. it's just...
I had big plans for us in June.

9
00:00:30.113 --> 00:00:33.325
I wanted to take some trips.
hit the beach.

10
00:00:33.951 --> 00:00:38.079
I also thought it could be awesome
if I just. like. stared at you a bunch.

11
00:00:38.080 --> 00:00:39.664
Aw. pimp...

12
00:00:39.665 --> 00:00:43.000
Are you gonna be depressed
all alone in this big house?

13
00:00:43.001 --> 00:00:45.086
It's just gonna be you and me. man.

14
00:00:45.087 --> 00:00:46.796
Big boy party. right?

15
00:00:46.797 --> 00:00:50.217
A couple of big boys doing big boy things.

16
00:00:50.801 --> 00:00:54.887
Big boys!

17
00:00:54.888 --> 00:00:56.973
You gotta move out of that pool house.

18
00:00:56.974 --> 00:00:58.641
Marisol must be going nuts.

19
00:00:58.642 --> 00:01:00.101
Yeah. it's not our favorite.

20
00:01:00.102 --> 00:01:03.896
Okay. maybe we should pump the brakes
on convincing other people

21
00:01:03.897 --> 00:01:05.481
to leave my dad
now that I'm leaving my dad?

22
00:01:05.482 --> 00:01:08.067
Guys. I'm gonna be absolutely fine.
I promise.

23
00:01:08.068 --> 00:01:10.528
You know how it's been super noisy
at my apartment

24
00:01:10.529 --> 00:01:12.238
because my mom's been training birds?

25
00:01:12.239 --> 00:01:13.531
- No.
- How would we know that?

26
00:01:13.532 --> 00:01:16.993
- I knew that.
- Maybe when Alice abandons you.

27
00:01:16.994 --> 00:01:18.202
I could move in here.

28
00:01:25.335 --> 00:01:27.295
Is it sad
that I just actually considered that?

29
00:01:27.296 --> 00:01:29.422
- Yeah. It's not great.
- You know where to find me. roomie.

30
00:01:32.509 --> 00:01:34.760
- You're not gonna leave. right. Sean?
- I'm never leaving. Jimmy.

31
00:01:34.761 --> 00:01:38.390
'Cause we are big boys.

32
00:01:39.391 --> 00:01:40.267
Oh.

33
00:01:40.851 --> 00:01:42.018
You just don't leave me like this.

34
00:01:42.019 --> 00:01:44.103
- Fine.
- There it is.

35
00:01:44.104 --> 00:01:46.522
See. it's gonna be like that every night.

36
00:01:46.523 --> 00:01:48.149
Hey. Maya.

37
00:01:48.150 --> 00:01:50.359
Got your message
about needing to skip this week.

38
00:01:50.360 --> 00:01:51.444
It's totally fine.

39
00:01:51.445 --> 00:01:54.071
Uh. but if you do that shit again.
I'm gonna find you.

40
00:01:54.072 --> 00:01:57.867
Give you therapy wherever you are.
gym. roller coaster. somebody else's bed.

41
00:01:57.868 --> 00:02:00.286
It does not matter to me.

42
00:02:00.287 --> 00:02:02.706
All right. bye.

43
00:02:06.126 --> 00:02:07.627
Okay. what's the damn emergency. Liz?

44
00:02:07.628 --> 00:02:09.377
Derek's mother's been here for two days.

45
00:02:09.378 --> 00:02:11.547
I'm already losing my shit.

46
00:02:11.548 --> 00:02:14.175
- Oh. what's she doing?
<i>- Nothing.</i>

47
00:02:14.176 --> 00:02:16.969
She's being perfectly kind.

48
00:02:16.970 --> 00:02:19.180
That's why she's an evil genius.

49
00:02:19.181 --> 00:02:21.557
<i>Do you know what
that bitch said to me this morning?</i>

50
00:02:21.558 --> 00:02:23.142
"Derek's lucky to have you."

51
00:02:23.143 --> 00:02:24.477
Well. that's rough.

52
00:02:24.478 --> 00:02:26.604
- What the hell's wrong with you?
- <i>You're not getting it.</i>

53
00:02:26.605 --> 00:02:31.067
She says the right words
with the right tone.

54
00:02:31.068 --> 00:02:35.947
and then she holds eye contact
for an extra few seconds

55
00:02:35.948 --> 00:02:39.200
<i>so I can feel
the judgment that no one else can.</i>

56
00:02:39.201 --> 00:02:40.326
Liz.

57
00:02:40.327 --> 00:02:41.869
Hold. hold. hold.

58
00:02:41.870 --> 00:02:43.037
Yeah?

59
00:02:43.038 --> 00:02:47.625
Hi. Do you. um. do you have any
of those popsicles that Derek loves?

60
00:02:47.626 --> 00:02:48.794
I gotcha.

61
00:02:58.637 --> 00:03:00.055
- What?
- Sorry. I...

62
00:03:00.806 --> 00:03:05.435
I don't know what you've been doing.
but you look gorgeous.

63
00:03:06.478 --> 00:03:07.479
Thank you.

64
00:03:13.610 --> 00:03:15.653
Could you feel that?

65
00:03:15.654 --> 00:03:17.488
Yeah. I gotta go. Liz.

66
00:03:20.701 --> 00:03:25.037
I had a nice loud voice
before Parkinson's.

67
00:03:25.038 --> 00:03:27.081
- I miss it.
- Yeah.

68
00:03:27.082 --> 00:03:29.834
And I hate all those vocal exercises.

69
00:03:29.835 --> 00:03:31.211
I hate 'em too.

70
00:03:32.546 --> 00:03:33.880
When I do the yelling one.

71
00:03:33.881 --> 00:03:39.468
I find it helps to yell about something
that really annoys me like. uh.

72
00:03:39.469 --> 00:03:41.971
"Kids shouldn't be
allowed in restaurants."

73
00:03:41.972 --> 00:03:43.973
- Oh. Yeah.
- Mmm.

74
00:03:43.974 --> 00:03:47.560
"Dick should not be short for Richard."

75
00:03:47.561 --> 00:03:50.104
"Twins confuse and frighten me."

76
00:03:50.105 --> 00:03:51.355
I like that one.

77
00:03:51.356 --> 00:03:52.773
Feels good.

78
00:03:52.774 --> 00:03:54.734
I'm trying to wind down my practice.

79
00:03:54.735 --> 00:03:59.531
and Sykes keeps sending me
these Parkinson's patients.

80
00:04:00.240 --> 00:04:02.742
They're not cheerful like I am.

81
00:04:02.743 --> 00:04:05.287
Yeah. I love how
you know yourself so well.

82
00:04:05.913 --> 00:04:08.456
Look. you're a positive role model.

83
00:04:08.457 --> 00:04:09.916
I'm very proud of you.

84
00:04:09.917 --> 00:04:11.542
Go on if you want.

85
00:04:11.543 --> 00:04:15.046
Are you feeling
a little sorry for yourself

86
00:04:15.047 --> 00:04:17.465
since your tremors have become bilateral?

87
00:04:17.466 --> 00:04:19.634
Now I got two shaky hands.

88
00:04:19.635 --> 00:04:22.845
I got 24-hour jazz hands.

89
00:04:22.846 --> 00:04:24.305
Fosse. Fosse. Fosse.

90
00:04:24.306 --> 00:04:27.517
All right.
That's a normal progression.

91
00:04:27.518 --> 00:04:29.936
But if you need to vent. it's okay.

92
00:04:29.937 --> 00:04:32.021
You... I mean. you can complain to me.

93
00:04:32.022 --> 00:04:34.774
I know that. and that's why I don't do it.

94
00:04:34.775 --> 00:04:38.110
Right. right. Because suffering in silence
makes you brave.

95
00:04:38.111 --> 00:04:40.696
and you want
to be the best there is at Parkinson's.

96
00:04:40.697 --> 00:04:42.365
Is that what they're saying?

97
00:04:42.366 --> 00:04:43.449
That I'm the best?

98
00:04:43.450 --> 00:04:44.534
Oh.

99
00:04:44.535 --> 00:04:45.993
Top ten at least.

100
00:04:58.465 --> 00:04:59.550
Ready?

101
00:05:12.062 --> 00:05:13.188
What?

102
00:05:14.273 --> 00:05:15.940
It's "brave." sweetie.

